The criterion (\ref{unc-rel viol}) arising from the present UR detects entanglement for $r_0<r<1$, with $r_0$ becoming closer to 1 --- a value which corresponds to the pure maximally entangled state (\ref{Phi+ ket}) --- as the dimensionality $N$ increases.  We remark that this does not mean that for other values of $r$ the state is not entangled.  Our measure establishes that $r$ being in the interval $(r_0, 1)$ is sufficient for the state to be entangled, but not necessary: there might be other values of $r$ for which the state is entangled.


